DATA CLOUD
Privacy Data Model

The Customer 360 Data Model privacy subject tracks and stores certain data privacy preferences. Keep in mind that deciding how to honor customer privacy preferences is up to you.

To view a larger version, right-click or control-click the image and select “Open Image in New Tab” or view the Privacy data model architecture.

These privacy DMOs are represented in Data Cloud.

DMO	DESCRIPTION	REFERENCE DOC LINK
Authorization Form Consent	A Data Cloud DMO for details about where, when, and how consent was granted for a specific form, set of terms and conditions, or privacy policy.	Authorization Form Consent DMO Reference
Communication Subscription	A Data Cloud DMO for a customer’s subscription preferences for a specific communication.	Communication Subscription DMO Reference
Communication Subscription Consent	A Data Cloud DMO for the engagement or communication channel preferences of a customer.	Communication Subscription Consent DMO Reference
Contact Point Consent	A Data Cloud DMO for individual consent preferences for a specific contact point, such as an email address, including double opt-in information.	Contact Point Consent DMO Reference
Engagement Channel Type Consent	A Data Cloud DMO for individual privacy preferences for a specific engagement channel, such as SMS or email.	Engagement Channel Type Consent DMO Reference
Party Consent	A Data Cloud DMO for individual’s consent preferences.	Party Consent DMO
Contact Consent Configuration
DMO	DESCRIPTION	REFERENCE DOC LINK
Authorization Form	A Data Cloud DMO for the set of terms and conditions, such as privacy policy, contract, or consent forms.	Authorization Form DMO Reference
Authorization Form Data Use	A Data Cloud DMO for the data uses consented to in an authorization form.	Authorization Form Data Use DMO Reference
Authorization Form Text	A Data Cloud DMO for an authorization form’s text and language settings.	Authorization Form Text DMO Reference
Communication Subscription Timing	A Data Cloud DMO for a customer's timing preferences for receiving a communication subscription.	Communication Subscription Timing DMO Reference
Data Use Purpose Consent Action	A Data Cloud DMO for individual consent preferences for consent actions, for example, sharing for a specific data use purpose, such as billing or service.	Data Use Purpose Consent Action DMO Reference
Contact Consent Setup
DMO	DESCRIPTION	REFERENCE DOC LINK
Communication Subscription Channel Type	A Data Cloud DMO for a specific engagement channel for reaching customers, such as SMS or email.	Communication Subscription Channel Type DMO Reference
Consent Action	A Data Cloud DMO for what a user consents to be done with their data, for example, data collection or web activity tracking.	Consent Action DMO Reference
Consent Status	A Data Cloud DMO for the status of consent, for example opted in or out of data collection.	Consent Status DMO Reference
Data Use Legal Basis	A Data Cloud DMO for the legal reason for contacting a customer, such as billing or contract.	Data Use Legal Basis DMO Reference
Data Use Purpose	A Data Cloud DMO for the purpose of contacting a prospect or customer, such as for billing, marketing, or surveys.	Data Use Purpose DMO Reference
Engagement
DMO	DESCRIPTION	REFERENCE DOC LINK
Engagement Channel Type	A Data Cloud DMO for the channels supported by individual preferences. For example, individuals can set consent preferences for SMS but not for a phone call.	Engagement Channel Type DMO Reference
